 Not a letter was stirring, not one of the horde;
 The hoodies were hung by the chimney with care,
 In hopes that a boymoder soon would be there;
 The homos were nestled all snug in their beds;
 While visions of shirtless men danced in their heads;
 And janny in her 'kerchief, and I in my cap,
 Had just settled our bans for a long winter's nap,
 When out in a thread there arose such a clatter,
 I sprang from my bed to see what was the matter.
 And off to the front page I flew right away,
 Clicked open the sticky to see what was at play.
 The style of special on the posts I beheld,
 Gave a hint of magic to the words that were spelled,
 When what to my wondering eyes did out poke,
 But a reposted meme of eight heckin' trans folk,
 From a rascally anon so well dressed and fly,
 I knew in a moment they must be a bi.
 More pent up than lescels the tranners they came,
 Anon whistled, and shouted, and called them by name:
 "Now, Hailey! now, Hunter! now Alice and Aiden!
 On, Lily! on, Liam! on, Chloe and Brayden!
 To the top of the page! to the top of the board!
 Now bump away! bump away! we won't be ignored!"

You know you're brainwormed, which is a good thing. Being in a good, mentally stable place before transitioning may be a sensible choice to make sure you don't immediately cave and detrans. These feelings of inadequacy will consume you if you let them, and weeding them out takes time and effort. Hard to overcome, but given some support and some personal progress you can overcome it. You can change your opinions of yourself. You can change plenty of your wants.
Tranners would however urge you to rather start sooner than later, because it improves your chances, and because there is a chance you will never feel ready. Never, ever set out to a loosely defined goal with ill defined preconditions like that. You will never feel ready then, and just append new arbitrary conditions when you will start for real. Set a clear, realistic, measurable goal. "When my BMI is 23 I will transition", for example. Stick to it, you will never feel adequate or prepared.

Do you feel disgusted by being a man? Would you pick to wake up as a cis woman tomorrow with no hesitation? If you were alone for life on a desert island and had male and female clothes and a lifetime supply of HRT sitting there, what would you do? Would you feel upset if a personality test guessed you're male? If there was a test to see for sure if you have gender dysphoria or not, what result would you hope for? Would you rather be the hottest hunk of a man to ever live or an average woman? Would you transition if everyone in society was totally fine with it? How about if you knew for sure you'd pass? Those are some questions you can ask yourself.

Try sitting down and getting calm and kind of meditative and tell yourself repeatedly, "I am a man." How does that make you feel? How about the same thing with "I am a woman."? If you try it with, "I am going to stay a man for the rest of my life, I will never transition and I will die as a man," how does that feel? What about, "that's it, I'm done fighting feeling this way, I'm going to start transitioning as soon as possible," how does that make you feel?

Just a few exercises to kind of see. It's not definitive or anything but it might help.

There might be something going on if you've always felt like you've just been playing a character and you've always been detached and never present and like you're looking at someone else when you look in the mirror. For me, it's definitely always been there and been a thorn in my side, but I finally stopped feeling denial a while back and admitted to myself that I'm trans, and ever since then I've felt some kind of relief not keeping it from myself and I've been taking better care of myself and caring more about my life and stuff, but at the same time I can't stop thinking about transitioning now and I want it more than anything. From easy to difficult
1. there are n lightbulbs that are either on or off in a circle. you can flip on/off a sequence of k consecutive lightbulbs. for which values of the pair (n,k) is it possible to obtain any configuration from any initial configuration?
2. (medium) we have n weights, the first one an integer number of kgs between 1 and 1 invlusively, the second between 1 and 2, the kth between 1 and k, the last between 1 and n kgs. The total weight is even. Prove that we can put some of the weights on one arm of a balance and the others on the others st it may be balanced.
3. (hard) there is an n by n square grid, and some of them are colored black, the others white, in each square we write the numbers of squares of the opposite color adjacent to it, including via a corner (how the king moves in chess)
Find the maximum possible sum of the numbers in the squares
4.(harder)
there are n+1 buckets labeled 0 through n
You start out with n tokens in bucket 0, and on a move can move one token to the right by a number of buckets that is less than or equal to the number tokens in the bucket it is departing from
(eg on the first move you can move a token to bucket n, or any number below that, than on the second, after you've removed a token from bucket 0, you can only send to bucket n-1 at most)

Show the minimum number of moves to move everything to bucket n is ceiling(n/1)+ceiling(n/2)+ ... + ceiling (n/n)
, where ceiling just takes the lowest integer greater than or equal to the input, eg ceiling(3.1)=ceiling(4)=4.

Goal of the thread: It is Christmas, don't forget to practice some self care!
Daily goals can be repeated. Remember to keep score, it can only go up!

>What is this thread for?
Getting better is hard, and sucks. A lot. It does not get easier doing it alone.
Share resources and experiences with combating depression, anxiety, personal issues, achieving or maintaining a healthy weight, etc.
>Why is this thread /lgbt/?
Struggles with mental and physical health are an indisputable part of /lgbt/ life, be it from dysphoria, social pressure, heartbreak, or just unfortunate lifestyle choices.
>Notes to consider:
Please be civil. Shame is your greatest enemy in fighting urges of self abuse (be it sh, drugs, or just self deprecation). Relapsing into bad and unhealthy habits is to be expected, the goal is to increase the average amount of time it takes between relapses. Any improvement is a victory no matter how small. Your worth and right to get better are non-negotiable. And most importantly:
WE ARE NOT THERAPISTS, WE DON'T REPLACE MEDICATION
>Note on advice
Generic advice won't necessarily help you in particular, but for those it does it is an essential foundation to build future progress on, not a miracle cure. Do not underestimate the effects subtle changes to your lifestyle can have. Try first, keep us posted on your progress, build from there.

If any resource below is unhelpful, please let me know. I can't assert their quality on my own.

A healthy goal! These types of social situations are difficult because in my experiences they usually arise from something lost in translation from a cultural or generational divide. One plausible explanation is that he considers you an adult now. Older generations and certain cultures have an implied expectation of adults "making themselves useful".
People often forget that the world around them changes, and that their sense of etiquette may not be as universal as it was when they were kids. As a consequence unfair "why didn't you read my mind" type of situations arise. To think of a miscommunication in terms of fault is unhelpful in that case, if your uncle is easy enough to talk to you could try figuring out his mindset.

Ohhh I see I see
Well, replacing sub with oral is a bit problematic, bcs you're going from higher avg/peak lvls w/sub to a lot lower with same mg sub to oral e2 dose.
to explain, oral takes awhile to buildup e2 lvls as your body is building up a reservoir of various sulfated/conjugated/weaker forms of estrogens that build up, which converts back to e2 making e2 lvls nice and steady plus higher e2 lvls on avg than single dose (takes a few weeks), and so if u rely on oral e2 without building up u can suddenly spike T lvls due to lacking antigonadatropin action of higher e2 like sub does.
so, it very well could of been a spike in T lvls, even just mid/high female T lvls, but that change from likely near zero T would be a bit of a shock to your system as likely sensitized ARs due to low T lvls for awhile+cypro being an AR antagonist

my advice in the future is to titrate your dose when changing it, so avoid that sudden shock like u experienced, and with oral e2 u wanna build up lvls first b4 relying on it

The use of pronouns is automatic and intrinsic in human nature. We look at someone and at a glance instantly decide if they're male or female, this is because of the threat identification response. In nature it's extremely important for survivability to be able to look at another creature and quickly assess if they're a threat or not. Are they male or female? Do they look angry? Are they holding a weapon? etc.

Neo pronouns are completely different, there are no natural human pathways for neo pronouns outside of cultural consideration. You have to consciously think and decide before speaking which pronouns to use until you are trained to do it naturally. Even she/her and he/him can become neo pronouns if you have to think about them before using them (ie because someone doesn't pass). I'm not even disparaging people that use neo pronouns this is just the reality of how they function.

They/them can only ever be a neo pronoun because there is no third gender in terms of biology. There is only male female or "not sure yet". Human beings do not really evolve anymore because there is no logic to advantageous mutation so outside the intervention of technology (nightmare lol) there will NEVER be a natural pronoun response to ANY other gender identities outside of the binary. You will NEVER look at a stranger and instantly identify them as non-binary. You will ONLY receive contextual clues based on how they look and present themselves and basically have to ask them or ask someone that knows them for their pronouns.
